                            <comment id="17235736" author="jira-bot" created="Thu, 19 Nov 2020 20:39:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 76d60548a8887f58afd6b535e09bfdb328229817 in qpid-jms&apos;s branch refs/heads/master from Timothy Bish&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=qpid-jms.git;h=76d6054&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=qpid-jms.git;h=76d6054&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPIDJMS-519&quot; title=&quot;Transational sends can be performed outside a transaction following connection recovery&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;QPIDJMS-519&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;QPIDJMS-519&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Correctly recover transaction after failover&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adds additional guards against allowing a send or acknowledge&lt;br/&gt;
to occur outside the bounds of a transaction when recovering a&lt;br/&gt;
connection following failover.  Adds tests to ensure that the&lt;br/&gt;
transaction becomes in-doubt whenever the state of recovery&lt;br/&gt;
cannot ensure that there will be no lost work or untransacted&lt;br/&gt;
work.  Test added to cover cases where this was previously seen.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
